name: The Munki Project
body:
### Welcome to Munki!
The Munki Project is home to several projects that are focused on improving the experience of managing OS X for both the admin and the end user. Munki is surrounded by a vibrant community that is passionate about the craft of managing OS X and the services that surround it.


### Munki Projects
* [Munki](https://www.munki.org/munki/)
* [MunkiWebAdmin](https://github.com/munki/munkiwebadmin)
* [createOSXInstallPkg](https://github.com/munki/createOSXinstallPkg)


### Community
Part of what makes Munki so popular is the fantastic community that surrounds it. If you want to get involved in the community, you can join the [mailing list](https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/munki-dev), pop into the [##osx-server IRC channel on Freenode](https://webchat.freenode.net/?randomnick=1&channels=%23%23osx-server) or come to one of many [Mac Admin conferences](https://github.com/munki/munki/wiki/More-Links-And-Tools#mac-admin-conferences) around the world.
